<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-12-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-12-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="463" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Willis</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 9.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-12-05"><hi rend="smallcaps">December</hi> 5,
                                    1893</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In this dispatch Mr. Willis speaks solely of the difficulty experienced
                            in translating; the naval cipher which he is obliged to use and suggests
                            that he be furnished with a simpler code.</p>
                    </div>
